1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
 - Amen, amen, awesome.

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:03,960
 Have a seat, have a seat.

3
00:00:03,960 --> 00:00:05,000
 Well, welcome to The Vine.

4
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,520
 If this is your first time with us ever,

5
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,080
 we're glad that you're here.

6
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:12,040
 If this is your first time with us in 2026,

7
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:14,000
 we're glad that you're here with us.

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,920
 We know that many people have been traveling

9
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,880
 and some of you are here with us

10
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:20,920
 for the first time this year, so welcome back.

11
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:23,240
 Last week, I introduced to us the idea

12
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:26,480
 that as a leadership here at The Vine in this season,

13
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:29,920
 the beginning of 26, we're feeling very led by the Lord

14
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:33,760
 to teach into the context of seasons of waiting

15
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,600
 and that the reality might be for you

16
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:39,600
 that you're either in a season of waiting right now

17
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,320
 or maybe you've just come out of one

18
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,080
 or you're gonna be heading into one,

19
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:44,880
 but for all of us, we know what it is

20
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:46,360
 to be in seasons of waiting,

21
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:48,600
 to struggle in the realities

22
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,640
 that we're waiting for something to happen

23
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:54,880
 that we expect it to happen but hasn't happened.

24
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:57,020
 And we believe that what the Holy Spirit wants to do

25
00:00:57,020 --> 00:00:59,240
 in the first part of this year for us

26
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:02,760
 is that Jesus wants to meet us pastorally

27
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:07,360
 and compassionately and powerfully renew our strength.

28
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,720
 So if you're in a season of waiting,

29
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:13,680
 this is a very encouraging next number of weeks for you,

30
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,960
 or if you're not, you may well enter into one

31
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,880
 in the near future and the things that we're gonna teach

32
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:22,640
 over this series will be helpful tools for you

33
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:25,680
 for the season that might be ahead.

34
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,440
 We shared last week that we don't like waiting

35
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:30,400
 as human beings, waiting is hard.

36
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,760
 In fact, in our modern world, in our modern context,

37
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:35,340
 we're now conditioned not to wait,

38
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:38,220
 that the idea is that things need to happen quickly

39
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:40,320
 and fast and that actually as human beings

40
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,860
 in this modern world that we live in,

41
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:45,480
 we put a very high value on the things that happen quickly.

42
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,440
 If something takes time or doesn't come as quickly

43
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:51,880
 as we would want it, we generally see that

44
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:54,680
 as something that we see lesser value in.

45
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,820
 So we have this driving sense

46
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:59,440
 that the good things come quickly

47
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:01,760
 and bad things or weak things

48
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:04,040
 or things that are not as valuable

49
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,800
 are often the things that take time.

50
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,240
 And we as Christians, we talked about last week,

51
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,720
 we brought this into our faith, haven't we?

52
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:13,920
 And we have this mindset that God needs to act

53
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,600
 and he needs to act immediately.

54
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,800
 And if God doesn't act immediately,

55
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,320
 then there's a, often in us as Christians,

56
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:25,320
 we devalue him, that we ask questions about him,

57
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:28,040
 that we second guess his nature.

58
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,880
 This is what we do as Christians

59
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:32,280
 when it seems like there's a delay,

60
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,760
 where there's a promise that we thought was gonna happen

61
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:37,320
 that didn't happen, there was a prayer for healing

62
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:40,000
 that we were hoping for that didn't seem to take place,

63
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,400
 that there was an expected word from God

64
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,520
 that didn't seem to come in the timeframe

65
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,720
 that we were expecting.

66
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:47,160
 We either will do one of two things.

67
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:51,040
 We will either doubt God and judge his character

68
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:54,260
 or we will often doubt ourselves and judge our own.

69
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:56,000
 Oh, there's some sin in me, there's some brokenness in me,

70
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,400
 there's something wrong with me,

71
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:01,200
 which is why God is not doing what I'm expecting him to do.

72
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,920
 And we saw last week that there are over 200 passages

73
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:06,320
 of scripture on the idea of waiting.

74
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:09,680
 And if you do a survey of those scriptures,

75
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:12,400
 basically generally what the passages of scripture teach us

76
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:16,120
 is that waiting in God's eyes is a gift.

77
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,880
 So it's a very different experience

78
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,000
 to how we think about it in the modern context

79
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,400
 and how often we've thought about it

80
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,520
 within our modern religious context,

81
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,880
 that actually waiting is a gift,

82
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:28,400
 that it enables us to experience something of God's pleasure

83
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,200
 or something of God's character

84
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,560
 that we may not have experienced otherwise,

85
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,880
 causes us to slow down,

86
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,520
 to reevaluate some of the things

87
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,960
 that are going on in our lives,

88
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,760
 to better bring that to the Lord as well,

89
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:44,640
 to strip away our sense of being God.

90
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:49,040
 Often seasons of waiting are a way of reducing my thought

91
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:51,360
 that I can provide fully for myself

92
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,320
 and realigns us to the reality

93
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,240
 that we need something else,

94
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,040
 that we need to trust in God,

95
00:03:57,040 --> 00:04:00,220
 that we need to wait and rely on Him

96
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:03,040
 to do what we cannot do.

97
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,280
 And we talked last week

98
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,880
 that we're gonna base this whole series,

99
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,240
 this next four or five weeks,

100
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,000
 in this idea of Psalm 27.

101
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,520
 Psalm 27, one of the most beautiful Psalms

102
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,640
 that we have in the book of Psalter,

103
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,160
 a Psalm of King David.

104
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,760
 And right at the end of that, he says,

105
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:17,960
 "Wait for the Lord."

106
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:19,600
 He encourages his people,

107
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,880
 "Wait for the Lord, be strong, take heart,

108
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,720
 "and wait for Him."

109
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:26,320
 And we saw last week that the word wait there

110
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,080
 is the Hebrew word kava.

111
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,160
 And kava means something very interesting.

112
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:33,280
 It means to bind together, to gather together,

113
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:36,320
 to look and to expect,

114
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,520
 which is a very different way

115
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:40,880
 that we think about waiting in our modern context.

116
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,520
 When we think about waiting,

117
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:46,200
 we predominantly think about it as inactivity.

118
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,680
 Like if I need to wait,

119
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:50,280
 it means that I'm not doing anything.

120
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:53,080
 I'm just kind of going, right?

121
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,880
 But in the Hebrew way of thinking,

122
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,840
 waiting is not inactivity or idleness.

123
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:02,200
 It is an active anticipation of change.

124
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,840
 Remember, we talked about this last week.

125
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,920
 It is an active anticipation of change.

126
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:09,160
 In other words, waiting is not this kind of like,

127
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,880
 "Oh gosh, I guess I'll just give up

128
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,320
 "and just kind of like do nothing."

129
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,600
 Waiting is like, I'm expecting.

130
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,520
 Oh, I don't know when it's coming.

131
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:18,880
 And sure, it can be hard and painful

132
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:21,240
 in the way I wish it was today,

133
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,200
 but it may not be,

134
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:25,360
 but I'm actively anticipating

135
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,280
 that there is going to be a change.

136
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:30,440
 That God, who is the same yesterday, today and forever,

137
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:34,440
 God whose character I can depend on is going to act.

138
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:37,360
 I hope it's now, but if it's not, and I need to wait,

139
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:41,160
 then I have an active anticipation that change is coming.

140
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:46,000
 Therefore, in the Hebrew thinking about waiting,

141
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,120
 waiting is like a prophetic act.

142
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,360
 It's not a,

143
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:56,520
 it is a, I'm going to live in such a way

144
00:05:56,520 --> 00:06:01,000
 that I am gonna prophetically live into the future

145
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,560
 of what I'm expecting God to do

146
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:07,640
 rather than the reality of my circumstance today.

147
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:09,160
 I'm not gonna ignore the fact,

148
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,160
 I'm not gonna downplay the reality that waiting is hard,

149
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,400
 but I'm gonna have an active anticipation

150
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:18,840
 of change in my spirit and a prophetic hope

151
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,320
 in the way in which, I almost fell over there,

152
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:22,680
 and a prophetic hope in the way

153
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,920
 in which I'm going to live my life, amen?

154
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:28,880
 So that's what we were kind of digging into last week.

155
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:31,320
 And we talked about the fact that Psalm 27

156
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,040
 has these four stanzas in it.

157
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,320
 It's a poem of four blocks,

158
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,760
 and we're gonna take one of those blocks

159
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,960
 over the next four weeks.

160
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:42,480
 And in each of the blocks, David does this beautiful thing.

161
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:47,440
 He shows us one of the negative aspects of waiting,

162
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,440
 and then he gives us his antidote to that negative thing

163
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,320
 in all four of these things.

164
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:54,600
 So as we go through this series over this month,

165
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,600
 you're gonna get a lot of tips and tools

166
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:59,080
 for those waiting seasons in your life.

167
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,160
 And today we're gonna start

168
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:03,560
 in the first three verses of Psalm 27.

169
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,920
 So let me read this to us together

170
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,280
 as we take a look at this first negative thing

171
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,280
 and David's hope within it.

172
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,340
 Psalm 27 verses one to three says,

173
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:17,400
 the Lord is my light and my salvation.

174
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,540
 Whom should I fear?

175
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:21,520
 The Lord is the stronghold of my life.

176
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,940
 Of whom should I be afraid?

177
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:28,120
 When evil doers came upon me to devour my flesh,

178
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,320
 when my adversaries and my enemies did,

179
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,240
 they stumbled and they fell.

180
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:37,200
 If an army encamps against me, my heart will not fear.

181
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,800
 If war rises up against me in spite of this,

182
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,640
 I am confident.

183
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:46,560
 There's this phenomenon in scripture, in biblical studies,

184
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,200
 you may not have heard of it before.

185
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,680
 It's a phenomenon where sometimes the best way

186
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:55,240
 to interpret a passage is actually to approach it in reverse.

187
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,340
 So working from the end towards the beginning.

188
00:07:58,340 --> 00:08:01,680
 This is often seen actually in Hebrew poetry.

189
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:04,520
 Hebrew poetry often has parallel isms to it

190
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,320
 and often the thought develops

191
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,440
 and sometimes what is said at the end

192
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:10,320
 is the interpretive framework

193
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,120
 for how you to understand the start.

194
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,500
 We even see this in the New Testament.

195
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:17,360
 Actually the apostle Paul is famous in writing this way

196
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:19,460
 and in some of his structures,

197
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:21,620
 what he says at the end is the key

198
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:23,120
 for understanding what he's been saying

199
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,400
 throughout the whole flow.

200
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,400
 And here we see a great example of this.

201
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,720
 So I'm gonna start in verse three

202
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:32,520
 and we're gonna work our way back to verse one

203
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:36,200
 as I unpack for you this negative thing

204
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,360
 that David mentions here,

205
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:41,040
 which is the idea of fear and anxiety.

206
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,480
 Verse three says this,

207
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:47,100
 if an army encamps against me, my heart will not fear.

208
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:51,900
 If war arises against me, in spite of this, I'm confident.

209
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,800
 David starts by saying something quite unique.

210
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:58,600
 He doesn't say what I would expect him to say.

211
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,960
 He's talking about armies, he's talking about wars,

212
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,120
 he's talking about battles

213
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,500
 and he's talking about the reality

214
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,920
 that so often in those things we fear,

215
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,520
 but he says this, he says,

216
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:11,200
 when a army encamps around me,

217
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,040
 or another way of interpreting Hebrew here,

218
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:17,240
 when rumors of war arise against me.

219
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:21,880
 So David is not speaking about the moment of the battle.

220
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:25,480
 He's not talking about war actually happening to him.

221
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,520
 He's not talking about like,

222
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,680
 hey, I'm in a battle right now

223
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:30,080
 and this battle is really hard

224
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,100
 and it's creating some fear in me.

225
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,960
 No, he's actually saying the opposite.

226
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:37,320
 He's saying, do you wanna know when I really fear?

227
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:40,600
 Do you wanna know when the enemy has the greatest door

228
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,080
 to get into my life and create fear within me?

229
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:45,560
 It's not when the battle is actually happening,

230
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,720
 it's the night before the battle.

231
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:52,840
 He's like, it's when the armies have encamped around me.

232
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,460
 They're camped around me.

233
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:58,000
 They haven't attacked yet, but they're threatening to.

234
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,200
 Are you with this?

235
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,320
 He's like, when the rumors of war arise against me,

236
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:06,000
 not the fight itself, but when I hear the rumors of it,

237
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,040
 that's when I can sense that fear begins to arise in me.

238
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,120
 And I think what David is doing here

239
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,520
 is helping us to understand something really important

240
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:16,180
 about seasons of waiting.

241
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:20,160
 That so often in seasons of waiting,

242
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:24,000
 the anticipation of what could happen

243
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,240
 creates more fear in us

244
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:30,040
 than the eventual reality of what does take place.

245
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,140
 Are you with me?

246
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:32,880
 This is anxiety.

247
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,040
 It's classic anxiety.

248
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:38,000
 And this is what happens when we wait.

249
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,400
 When we're waiting for the doctor to get back to us

250
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,920
 about what's going on in us,

251
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:44,560
 maybe we've got a blood test in there

252
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,600
 or whatever it might be.

253
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,680
 We're waiting for the doctor to get back to us.

254
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:50,760
 What happens is all this fear rises inside of us

255
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:53,720
 and we start to spirally think in our minds

256
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,160
 that the worst case scenario is gonna happen.

257
00:10:56,160 --> 00:11:00,400
 And oftentimes, the longer the wait,

258
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,800
 the greater the anxiety.

259
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,720
 Have you noticed that in your life?

260
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,160
 So you're waiting.

261
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,960
 Maybe there's a hard conversation with someone

262
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,520
 that you need to have at work.

263
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:11,160
 And the longer it takes to have that conversation,

264
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:14,320
 the worse you think they're going to react.

265
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,380
 Or maybe you're waiting for a spouse

266
00:11:16,380 --> 00:11:18,200
 or you've been praying for a long time

267
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,920
 for a new special relationship in your life,

268
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,760
 but the longer the wait goes,

269
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,880
 the more you begin to think

270
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,920
 it's never going to happen to you.

271
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:29,600
 David's saying, "It's when the armies are encamped around me

272
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,760
 "that I have anxiety

273
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:35,480
 "because I often fear the worst case scenario.

274
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:39,400
 "And so often, that is the thing that grips my heart."

275
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:42,440
 And the reality is, in seasons of waiting

276
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,640
 in all of our lives,

277
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:47,080
 this is the first thing that the enemy brings against us.

278
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:50,160
 I talked last week about the four emotional states

279
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:55,120
 of waiting, confusion, anxiety, hopelessness, self-pity.

280
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,280
 We're looking at this particular position

281
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,240
 of anxiety here this morning.

282
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,800
 This anxiety gets in us

283
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,320
 because we're beginning to extrapolate

284
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:05,400
 the worst case scenario

285
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,440
 because the waiting is going on.

286
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:11,200
 And that's what David is trying to describe here.

287
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:14,500
 And he's saying, "I know that kind of pain.

288
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,500
 "I know that kind of anxiety.

289
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:19,560
 "I've kind of felt this kind of anxiety."

290
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,200
 The reality of the wait.

291
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,920
 And what I think David is saying is this,

292
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:26,000
 "Before you fight a battle in the flesh,

293
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,000
 "you're going to need to first fight a battle in your mind."

294
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,320
 Come on, church.

295
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,160
 Like before you actually have to

296
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,000
 maybe do that hard conversation

297
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,560
 or before you actually do get the results from the doctor,

298
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,840
 whichever way it might go,

299
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:42,240
 the first battle is always the battle of the mind.

300
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,320
 And when you're in seasons of waiting,

301
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,720
 it is your mind that the enemy is going to grab ahold of.

302
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:51,760
 And David's like, "You got to understand this."

303
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,880
 But then he says, "There are two ways

304
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,720
 "that you beat the battle of the mind."

305
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:59,160
 So if this is connecting with you,

306
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,200
 and you're like, "I know what it is

307
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,840
 "to have this battle going on in here.

308
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:05,240
 "That so often I have the worst case scenario."

309
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,080
 And you know what?

310
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:06,920
 So often that doesn't happen,

311
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:10,160
 but man, the anxiety and the fear and the stress of it all

312
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,640
 because of what's been going around him.

313
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,040
 If you know what it is to have a battle of the mind,

314
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,400
 David says there are two primary ways

315
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,540
 to beat the battle of the mind.

316
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:20,800
 The first is found in verse two.

317
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:26,240
 He says, "When evil doers came upon me to devour my flesh,

318
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,240
 "my adversaries and my enemies,

319
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,840
 "they stumbled and they fell."

320
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:33,080
 In some modern translations,

321
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,040
 the NIV that I often read from,

322
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,360
 this is actually in the present tense,

323
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:38,360
 but if you read it in the Hebrew, it's in the past tense,

324
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,440
 and that's really important.

325
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,320
 Because what actually David is communicating here is,

326
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:45,400
 here's the first way that you begin to win

327
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:48,240
 the battle of mind when it comes to anxiety and fear.

328
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,400
 He's like, "Sometimes we can't avoid the reality

329
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,720
 "that anxiety and fear will come to us."

330
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,960
 'Cause so often they're the first emotion

331
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,900
 that arises in us, right?

332
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,240
 But he's saying, you wanna know how you beat that?

333
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,880
 You wanna know how you begin to process it in a healthy way?

334
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:04,760
 How you begin to get over that fear and that anxiety?

335
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:08,160
 He says, "There have been times before,

336
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,920
 "when the enemies have encircled me.

337
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:12,400
 "Oh, there have been times before

338
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,380
 "when my adversaries have attacked me,

339
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:17,240
 "but they stumbled and fell.

340
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,900
 "In the past, they were defeated.

341
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:22,520
 "In the past, they did not win."

342
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,280
 And I need, David is saying to himself,

343
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,880
 "I need to remember today."

344
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,400
 'Cause this is a battle of the mind.

345
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,840
 So I need to get my mind to think on something

346
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,600
 other than the fear of what I think is going to happen.

347
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,480
 And one of the ways that I overcome it is I go,

348
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:40,040
 "Hang on, I've been in this situation before.

349
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:44,000
 "And the Lord stood by me last time.

350
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,420
 "That the Lord equipped me and strengthened me and helped me.

351
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:50,320
 "And I saw before my enemies fall.

352
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:54,320
 "And what he's done before, I believe he can do it again."

353
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,040
 Didn't we just sing that song?

354
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,600
 Didn't we all go, "Woo-hoo, God's gonna do it again."

355
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:03,600
 But so often, we struggle with this and anxiety remains.

356
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:06,820
 And I love the fact that David is like,

357
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:09,380
 "The first thing we grab a hold of

358
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:11,500
 "is a reality that we must remember.

359
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,000
 "But I want you to know this.

360
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,960
 "One of the most destructive things about fear

361
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:19,160
 "is that it creates forgetfulness."

362
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,880
 I'm gonna say that again.

363
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,560
 Some of you need to write that down.

364
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:26,320
 That's a fridge magnet going on your fridge.

365
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:31,360
 Sometimes one of the most destructive things about fear

366
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:34,840
 is that it causes or creates forgetfulness.

367
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:38,080
 And because fear is present to us and right in front of us,

368
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:40,080
 and we're seeing all these things that are happening,

369
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,240
 we begin to forget what God has done before.

370
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,100
 We begin to forget that his promises

371
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:46,600
 have stood with us in the past.

372
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:49,160
 We begin to forget the battles that he fought for us

373
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,720
 and that he won before.

374
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:54,960
 And fear causes us to forget God's before

375
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:58,080
 so that we don't think we have him in the now.

376
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:01,480
 One of the enemy's greatest strategies

377
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:05,280
 against the church is spiritual amnesia.

378
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,200
 Come on, church.

379
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,560
 Spiritual amnesia.

380
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:13,200
 That we forget that God has been good.

381
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:16,920
 Which is why it was great a moment ago

382
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:20,320
 for us to hear from one another that God is still at work.

383
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,640
 That God is active.

384
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:25,600
 That he is doing something.

385
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:29,120
 This idea of causing and calling the church

386
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:31,360
 to remember the things that God has done

387
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,360
 is a consistent thread in scripture.

388
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:36,080
 I wanna just give you a quick New Testament example

389
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:39,200
 from Peter writing to his church.

390
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,120
 His church, in a season of great anxiety,

391
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:45,600
 they were believing that Jesus was gonna return soon.

392
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,480
 So Jesus has gone to the cross.

393
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,240
 He's raised from the dead.

394
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,400
 He's then met them.

395
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,360
 He's ascended.

396
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:54,040
 Before he met them, he said, "I will be returning to you."

397
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,640
 And so they have this idea

398
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,960
 that Jesus is gonna return soon,

399
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,920
 but he hasn't come back yet,

400
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,720
 and their lives are difficult and tough.

401
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:04,320
 And they realize if Jesus could come back,

402
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,960
 everything in my life is gonna be better.

403
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,280
 And the wait for Jesus to return

404
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,880
 is creating anxiety in the church.

405
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,480
 And Peter writes these words in 2 Peter 3.

406
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,000
 He says, "Dear friends,

407
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,420
 this is now my second letter to you.

408
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:21,840
 I have written both of them as reminders

409
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:25,200
 to stimulate you to wholesome thinking."

410
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,440
 Isn't that beautiful?

411
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:29,760
 "I want you to recall the words spoken in the past

412
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:32,400
 by the holy prophets and the command given

413
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,000
 by our Lord and Savior through the apostles."

414
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,880
 Verse 80 says, "But do not forget this one thing,

415
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:42,360
 dear friends, with the Lord a day is like a thousand years,

416
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:44,200
 and a thousand years are like a day."

417
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:47,360
 A great thing when we're thinking about waiting.

418
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,060
 But notice the three things he says here.

419
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:51,220
 And he goes, "I don't want you to forget.

420
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:52,420
 I want you to recall.

421
00:17:52,420 --> 00:17:54,420
 I write this as a reminder."

422
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:56,900
 In other words, we often do forget.

423
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,420
 We often do forget what God has done in the past.

424
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,540
 And when we forget what he's done in the past,

425
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:03,860
 we often struggle to think that he can act now.

426
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:06,160
 If you are in a season of waiting

427
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:11,140
 and you know that anxiety and fear is part of that season,

428
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:13,340
 one of the greatest and most powerful tools

429
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:15,820
 God has given you is your ability

430
00:18:15,820 --> 00:18:19,420
 to remember his goodness in the past

431
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:22,860
 and see that as a deposit to his faithfulness

432
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:23,960
 for you in the future.

433
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,720
 It's one of the most powerful tools you will have

434
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:29,780
 to overcome anxiety and fear in your life,

435
00:18:29,780 --> 00:18:32,700
 particularly in seasons of waiting.

436
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:36,220
 So the first thing he says is you need to remember.

437
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:38,460
 And if you've forgotten,

438
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:42,060
 it's because fear probably has caused you to forget.

439
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:46,540
 Go back, remember, and hold on as deposit

440
00:18:46,540 --> 00:18:49,280
 to God's faithfulness in the here and now.

441
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:51,020
 But there's another one.

442
00:18:51,020 --> 00:18:51,860
 That's the first one.

443
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:54,700
 Here's the second one found in verse one.

444
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:58,380
 It says, "The Lord is my light and my salvation.

445
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:00,020
 Whom should I fear?

446
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:01,660
 The Lord is the stronghold of my life.

447
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:04,700
 Of whom shall I be afraid?"

448
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:08,060
 It's really quite beautiful what David does.

449
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:09,200
 When you see this in the Hebrew,

450
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:12,920
 he starts the poem with the first Hebrew word, obviously,

451
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:15,600
 but the first word is this word Lord.

452
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,600
 It's in capital letters when you read it

453
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,060
 in our English translations.

454
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:23,200
 It's the name of God that is personal

455
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,240
 to the people of Israel.

456
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:27,480
 It's Yahweh as we come to understand it.

457
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:30,760
 And it literally means I am that I am,

458
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:32,220
 or more regularly thought of

459
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:33,800
 within the Jewish community at the time.

460
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:37,880
 Just this idea of God being the I am God.

461
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:40,040
 Now, it's interesting because King David

462
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:43,080
 could have chosen other names for God at the start.

463
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,800
 The other one that was very popular

464
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,240
 and used at the time was Elohim,

465
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:49,240
 which also means God for the Jewish people.

466
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:53,320
 But Yahweh, the Lord, was their personal expression

467
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,220
 of who God was.

468
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:57,560
 Going back, of course, to Moses at the burning bush

469
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,840
 where he meets with this God for the first time,

470
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:02,260
 and he asks this God, "What's your name?"

471
00:20:02,260 --> 00:20:04,400
 And God replies, "I am that I am."

472
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,820
 He gives the sacred name of the Jewish people.

473
00:20:06,820 --> 00:20:09,400
 Now, the Jewish people cannot say that name,

474
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,920
 but they know that that name,

475
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:12,120
 'cause that's part of the reverence of it,

476
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:15,280
 but they know that that name means I am.

477
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,660
 So I want you to notice something really interesting

478
00:20:17,660 --> 00:20:19,280
 that David does here in this Psalm.

479
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:24,280
 He starts by saying, "God is for us and for me

480
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:28,940
 "the I am God."

481
00:20:28,940 --> 00:20:32,840
 Which is interesting 'cause he's told us in verse two

482
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,080
 that one of the ways that you do the battle of the mind

483
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:38,260
 and one of the ways that you help process anxiety

484
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:40,940
 and fear in your life in seasons of waiting

485
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,580
 is by remembering what God has done in the past.

486
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:47,580
 But he starts by saying, "We don't worship,"

487
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:50,180
 come on, church, "a God fully in the past."

488
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:51,680
 He's like, "We gotta understand that the God

489
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:55,400
 "who has revealed himself to us is the great I am.

490
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:58,480
 "He's not actually the I was."

491
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,560
 Are you with me?

492
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,740
 Which is amazing 'cause David is trying

493
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:03,940
 to broaden our thinking.

494
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:07,260
 He's saying, "Yes, we need to look at God in the past,"

495
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:09,300
 but he's like, "I'm gonna start this by telling you this.

496
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:14,160
 "He is my God in the present, in the waits.

497
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:15,460
 "He is still the same.

498
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:19,180
 "He declares himself as I am.

499
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:25,720
 "He is not I was good, he's saying I am good.

500
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:28,840
 "He's not saying I was present,

501
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:33,840
 "he's saying I am present right here and right now."

502
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:36,500
 So he makes this declaration right at the start

503
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,220
 that God is here.

504
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:42,760
 And some of us need to recognize

505
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,520
 that in order to win the battle of the mind,

506
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:48,000
 yes, 100%, we need to remember

507
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,880
 what God's faithfulness was in the past

508
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:53,280
 and hold onto that in the present.

509
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:56,880
 But we have to be really careful in seasons of waiting

510
00:21:56,880 --> 00:22:00,640
 that we don't end up worshiping an I was God.

511
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,980
 Come on, all right?

512
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:07,520
 That we don't end up worshiping an I was God,

513
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:10,680
 that we worship an I am God in the here and now.

514
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:15,140
 That the one who did something amazing for me

515
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:18,400
 is the one who's present in this moment here.

516
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,360
 Even though it feels like he's distant,

517
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:23,000
 even if I haven't received the word,

518
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,240
 even if the promise hasn't come through,

519
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,000
 even if I'm still waiting,

520
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,640
 I declare not that I worship an I was God

521
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,320
 of some time in my past,

522
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:34,400
 as grateful as I am that God did that work then.

523
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:37,000
 And as much as I believe it's a deposit in faith

524
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,120
 for what's happening now,

525
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:41,620
 I need to declare that God is here in the wait.

526
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:46,560
 So David begins with the I am God.

527
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,440
 And then he says, notice this,

528
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:53,120
 "The Lord, the I am, is my light and my salvation.

529
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,440
 Whom should I fear?

530
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,880
 The Lord is the stronghold of my life."

531
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:57,700
 I love this.

532
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:00,460
 David gets personal right at the start.

533
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:02,460
 This is really important because

534
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:04,620
 what David's trying to do for his people

535
00:23:04,620 --> 00:23:07,660
 is not teach doctrine to them.

536
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:08,500
 He's not trying to say,

537
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:12,140
 "Guys, here are some things you need to believe about God,

538
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:15,740
 whether you have this relationship with him or not."

539
00:23:15,740 --> 00:23:20,980
 Instead, he's saying, Israel, who he's writing this psalm to,

540
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:22,500
 he's saying, "I want you to understand

541
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:26,340
 that the great I am is my God.

542
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:27,660
 He's my God.

543
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:30,620
 And I have experienced some things about him

544
00:23:30,620 --> 00:23:32,240
 that I need to declare to you,

545
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:35,180
 like the testimonies that we declared to one another earlier.

546
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:38,100
 He is my light," he says.

547
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:40,500
 "He is my salvation.

548
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:41,900
 He is my stronghold.

549
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:45,020
 He's the stronghold of my life.

550
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:46,700
 This has happened to me personally,

551
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:50,620
 and I felt it, and I see him at work in me."

552
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:54,660
 He's like, "I'm not standing here and saying,

553
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:59,420
 'Yahweh is the light,'" which is true.

554
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:03,100
 He doesn't say, "Yahweh is the salvation," which is true.

555
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:03,940
 He doesn't even say,

556
00:24:03,940 --> 00:24:07,060
 "Yahweh is the stronghold of all of our lives."

557
00:24:07,060 --> 00:24:08,820
 He says, "No, he's my light.

558
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:10,180
 He's my salvation.

559
00:24:10,180 --> 00:24:12,260
 He's my stronghold."

560
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:14,860
 In other words, I have experienced him

561
00:24:14,860 --> 00:24:18,700
 at work before and at work now doing these things.

562
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:21,720
 And many of us here, that's important,

563
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,740
 that the invitation of a season of waiting

564
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:28,640
 is an invitation into deeper personal connection with him.

565
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:33,260
 It's not the light, it's my light.

566
00:24:33,260 --> 00:24:34,220
 It's not the salvation.

567
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:36,440
 It's like, I know that salvation.

568
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,900
 I felt that salvation.

569
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:40,960
 I am feeling that salvation.

570
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:44,740
 And I'm gonna declare the I am,

571
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:48,940
 not simply the I was.

572
00:24:48,940 --> 00:24:49,820
 And what is he declaring?

573
00:24:49,820 --> 00:24:54,460
 Notice, light, salvation, stronghold.

574
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:58,260
 These three things that David mentions,

575
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:02,120
 I think are so beautiful because you can almost sense

576
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:05,460
 David's very personal sharing with his people.

577
00:25:05,460 --> 00:25:07,620
 He's talking about anxiety and fear.

578
00:25:07,620 --> 00:25:09,980
 He's talking about the reality of fear in the waiting.

579
00:25:09,980 --> 00:25:13,040
 And he says, "I've found a God,

580
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,320
 and I have a relationship with a God

581
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:19,580
 who is light and salvation and a stronghold

582
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:23,900
 in times of waiting where fear and anxiety are present."

583
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:26,260
 All three of these things that he mentions here

584
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:29,260
 speak immediately in the opposite

585
00:25:29,260 --> 00:25:31,700
 to what fear and anxiety are trying to do.

586
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:34,220
 See, fear and anxiety is always gonna try

587
00:25:34,220 --> 00:25:36,500
 and keep you in the darkness.

588
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:39,300
 It's always gonna cause you to retreat.

589
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,460
 It's always going to put a shadow

590
00:25:41,460 --> 00:25:43,700
 over your hopes and expectations.

591
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:45,980
 Fear and anxiety's primary purpose

592
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:47,540
 is to keep you in the dark.

593
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:53,620
 So it's not a surprise that David says, "He is my light."

594
00:25:53,620 --> 00:25:56,060
 "I know what it is to have seasons of darkness,"

595
00:25:56,060 --> 00:25:57,400
 I think David is saying,

596
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,580
 "but I wanna declare before you all

597
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:02,540
 that he is the one who has shone a light in that darkness."

598
00:26:02,540 --> 00:26:05,980
 And if you've ever struggled with fear or anxiety,

599
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:08,500
 you'll know what it is to sense that creeping

600
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:11,540
 sort of sense of depression that it brings alongside of it.

601
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:13,860
 That darkness, the sadness, the heaviness,

602
00:26:13,860 --> 00:26:17,140
 that I wanna just retreat into my bedroom

603
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:18,580
 and put myself under my covers

604
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:21,640
 and just kind of hope the day goes away.

605
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:25,860
 Anxiety and fear will drive you into the shadows.

606
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,380
 He is, David says, "My light."

607
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:31,820
 He then says salvation,

608
00:26:31,820 --> 00:26:33,740
 which when we read that in our modern context,

609
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:35,600
 it's so funny, we often will read that

610
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,660
 in a New Testament context.

611
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:39,960
 When we think of salvation, we immediately go to the cross

612
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:42,000
 and forgiveness of sin and Jesus's power

613
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:42,900
 and then his resurrection.

614
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:45,500
 That's what the word salvation rises for us,

615
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:46,980
 but we gotta remember that David is using this

616
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:49,500
 in a very different time and in a very different season.

617
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:53,100
 The word in Hebrew means rescuer or deliverer.

618
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:56,620
 And one of the things that fear and anxiety does to us

619
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:59,180
 is it binds us in chains.

620
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:01,380
 It binds our thinking.

621
00:27:01,380 --> 00:27:04,900
 It binds our view of the world.

622
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:08,660
 It binds and chains us away from hope,

623
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:12,380
 from energy, from wanting to do more.

624
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:15,000
 Fear and anxiety causes us to retreat, yes,

625
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,860
 but it then shackles us in that place of retreat.

626
00:27:17,860 --> 00:27:20,480
 And David says, "I know a God who has met me

627
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:23,260
 "in fear and anxiety in seasons of waiting on my life,

628
00:27:23,260 --> 00:27:25,560
 "and he has broken the chains.

629
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:30,240
 "He has been my rescuer, my deliverer,

630
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:35,040
 "the salvation from the things that were bound upon me."

631
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:37,080
 And then I love this last one.

632
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:39,520
 He says, "He's the stronghold of my life."

633
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:43,040
 The word here literally means he is my fortress.

634
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:46,400
 It's a military term, which is really fascinating.

635
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:49,440
 He starts, verse one, "He's my fortress."

636
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:52,000
 He's like, what it was in the military

637
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,640
 was that often either your soldiers

638
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:57,720
 would surround you with their shields

639
00:27:57,720 --> 00:28:00,920
 and create a fortress by which you would be protected,

640
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:03,040
 whether from arrows, whether from attacks,

641
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,560
 or literally they would create a building,

642
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:08,160
 a structure of high walls,

643
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:09,720
 and they would hide behind that

644
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:12,500
 and be safe in that dwelling place,

645
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:15,240
 being safe in that fortress.

646
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,240
 So it's fascinating.

647
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:20,400
 He takes this military term, he applies it to the I am,

648
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,340
 and he says, "I want you to know

649
00:28:21,340 --> 00:28:26,340
 "that I have experienced personally God surrounding me."

650
00:28:26,340 --> 00:28:29,840
 Now remember, he then goes on in verse three

651
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:32,440
 to say, "My enemies surround me."

652
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:34,560
 But he's like, you gotta remember,

653
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,960
 yes, my enemies surround me,

654
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:39,100
 but there's someone who's surrounding me before that.

655
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:42,780
 He's like, "I am encamped by the Holy Spirit.

656
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:45,740
 "I am encamped by the great I am.

657
00:28:45,740 --> 00:28:48,980
 "I am, I know that He is the stronghold,

658
00:28:48,980 --> 00:28:51,520
 "the one who surrounds and upholds me,"

659
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,240
 as we sing in that beautiful song

660
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,440
 that Promise and the team wrote,

661
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:57,120
 "As He surrounds and He upholds me,

662
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:59,420
 "yes, my enemies might surround me,

663
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,800
 "but they can't get to me

664
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:05,720
 "'cause I'm surrounded by Yahweh, by the great I am."

665
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:10,660
 And Christians who move with the blood of Jesus upon us

666
00:29:10,660 --> 00:29:13,660
 and the salvation of Christ purchased

667
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:15,380
 by that work on the cross,

668
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:19,540
 we are surrounded by the forgiveness and grace and mercy

669
00:29:19,540 --> 00:29:20,980
 of the power of the blood,

670
00:29:20,980 --> 00:29:23,980
 that the same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead

671
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:26,300
 is now in me.

672
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:31,720
 So David says, "I know what it is to fear and have anxiety.

673
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:36,020
 "Remember the past, remember what God has done

674
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:39,340
 "and hold onto that and don't let fear cause forgetfulness

675
00:29:39,340 --> 00:29:41,720
 "and spiritual amnesia in you.

676
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:45,340
 "But don't worship a God of the past.

677
00:29:45,340 --> 00:29:47,040
 "He's a God of the here and now.

678
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:50,200
 "He is the great I am and I know His light.

679
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:52,160
 "I know His deliverance.

680
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,080
 "I know that He's a stronghold,

681
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:56,240
 "more powerful than the encamping around me

682
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:57,860
 "that my enemies could ever do.

683
00:29:57,860 --> 00:30:00,400
 "So in my seasons of weight," he says,

684
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,880
 "whom shall I fear?

685
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:05,500
 "Of whom should I be afraid?

686
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:10,760
 "I am still confident," he says,

687
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:13,760
 "even when my enemies surround me."

688
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:18,680
 It's very personal for David.

689
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:20,400
 This psalm is very personal for me.

690
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:23,240
 I've shared with you before that one of the things

691
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:25,720
 that I struggle with is anxiety in my life.

692
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,840
 And this has been something that's been a battle

693
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:31,840
 for most of my adult life, so for the last 30 years.

694
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:33,440
 It's something that's in my family.

695
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:35,440
 It's a hereditary thing to some degree.

696
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:38,040
 My great-grandfather had it, my grandfather had it,

697
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:41,240
 my father had it, me and my siblings struggle with it.

698
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:43,800
 Anxiety is a very real thing for us.

699
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,420
 In fact, just over the last few months,

700
00:30:45,420 --> 00:30:47,680
 my anxiety flares up in seasons,

701
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,040
 often in seasons of waiting.

702
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:51,820
 I'm in a season of waiting for something that,

703
00:30:51,820 --> 00:30:54,520
 I don't wanna talk about it to you all today,

704
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,600
 but I'm in a season of waiting for something

705
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,160
 and I've really struggled with anxiety

706
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,000
 in the last couple of months.

707
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,600
 I remember just a few weeks ago,

708
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:04,560
 lying in bed late at night, not being able to sleep,

709
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:07,400
 and praying, and really praying.

710
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,200
 It's probably easy to think that a pastor

711
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:11,440
 is like a direct line to God, we don't.

712
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:16,760
 I wish that was the case all the time, but it's not.

713
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:19,880
 But I was praying in bed late at night, not sleeping,

714
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:23,160
 struggling with some insomnia 'cause of my anxiety

715
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:24,460
 in this season of waiting.

716
00:31:24,460 --> 00:31:27,660
 And long before we were studying this passage,

717
00:31:27,660 --> 00:31:31,220
 I felt like the Lord's saying, "I'm your light, Andrew.

718
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:36,360
 "I'm your salvation, your rescuer.

719
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:39,640
 "I am your deliverer, I am your stronghold."

720
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:41,800
 And I remember being flooded with peace.

721
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:46,680
 And the anxiety has continued at times,

722
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:49,800
 and the peace has continued alongside of it.

723
00:31:49,800 --> 00:31:52,240
 And I can stand before you today and say,

724
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:54,940
 "The great I am is my light.

725
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:57,400
 "He is my salvation.

726
00:31:57,400 --> 00:32:00,620
 "He is my stronghold in my life."

727
00:32:00,620 --> 00:32:02,860
 And I'm still waiting for the thing that I'm praying about,

728
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:04,520
 and believing, and hoping for,

729
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:06,780
 and I'm finding it anxious to be in the wait.

730
00:32:06,780 --> 00:32:11,000
 But I will remember a God who has done great things

731
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,480
 for me in the past, and I will stand

732
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:18,440
 on the great I am today, and I will have confidence in this,

733
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:20,420
 that I will see the goodness of the Lord

734
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:22,520
 in the land of the living, amen?

735
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,360
 - Amen. - Amen.

736
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:27,120
 (congregation applauding)

737
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,440
 I wonder whether you could stand with me,

738
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,180
 and I would love to pray for us.

739
00:32:30,180 --> 00:32:38,880
 And maybe you'd be happy just to put yourself

740
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,540
 in a posture of receiving.

741
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:45,920
 The Holy Spirit is present with us

742
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:48,900
 so beautifully this morning.

743
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:54,480
 And He is here to meet you.

744
00:32:58,200 --> 00:32:59,960
 And perhaps this has really been resonating with you.

745
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:02,760
 You know that journey of anxiety and fear

746
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,840
 within the waiting for yourself.

747
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,560
 Maybe it's not every day, but you know

748
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:09,500
 that there are moments where that's been there.

749
00:33:09,500 --> 00:33:11,880
 Maybe for some of you, it's a present reality

750
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,000
 right here and now.

751
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:17,440
 Father, I pray for every person here

752
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:23,800
 that we stand together as a community of faith

753
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:26,900
 on behalf of ourselves personally, but also one another.

754
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:32,740
 And Lord, where fear and anxiety has created forgetfulness,

755
00:33:32,740 --> 00:33:37,420
 Father, we pray right now for each person here

756
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:42,420
 that they would see again, remember again, hear again.

757
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:50,140
 So I'm praying, I just sense that the Spirit is saying

758
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:52,460
 that some of you are listening more to the wait

759
00:33:52,460 --> 00:33:54,660
 than you are to the Word.

760
00:33:54,660 --> 00:33:57,080
 (soft music)

761
00:33:57,080 --> 00:34:01,860
 Father, for those of us who where it's easy

762
00:34:01,860 --> 00:34:05,760
 for us to forget your Word in the loudness of the wait,

763
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:11,720
 Lord, would you help us release our spiritual amnesia?

764
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:15,460
 Would we celebrate what you have done before

765
00:34:15,460 --> 00:34:17,360
 and believe that you will do it again?

766
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:22,460
 And Lord, for every one of us, you are the great I am.

767
00:34:23,940 --> 00:34:25,540
 We don't worship a God of the past,

768
00:34:25,540 --> 00:34:27,140
 we worship a God of the present.

769
00:34:27,140 --> 00:34:32,700
 So Father, I wanna pray for light to shine in

770
00:34:32,700 --> 00:34:35,680
 to any darkness where fear and anxiety has taken hold.

771
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:41,140
 Father, I wanna pray for deliverance and rescue

772
00:34:41,140 --> 00:34:45,680
 for anyone who feels that they're bound in chains by fear.

773
00:34:45,680 --> 00:34:50,980
 And Father, we pray for a surrounding

774
00:34:50,980 --> 00:34:54,140
 and an upholding by you,

775
00:34:54,140 --> 00:34:59,300
 greater than the sense of our enemies around us.

776
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:01,860
 And maybe for some of you, that's the reality right now,

777
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:03,360
 you are in a difficult season

778
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,880
 and it feels like things have surrounded you,

779
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:09,520
 that feel overwhelming and difficult.

780
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:13,580
 The Lord wants you to know that He surrounds you,

781
00:35:13,580 --> 00:35:17,760
 closer than your enemies surround you,

782
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,520
 and He will deliver you.

783
